## 9. Styling Rules (DaisyUI)

Per `designbook-css-daisyui` SKILL.md:

- **All styling uses Tailwind CSS utility classes and DaisyUI component classes exclusively** — no custom CSS
- Allowed: `btn`, `card`, `badge`, `navbar`, `hero`, `menu`, `bg-primary`, `text-lg`, `p-4`, `flex`, `gap-2`, `rounded-lg`, `md:text-xl`, `lg:grid-cols-3`, etc.
- Not allowed: Custom CSS files, inline styles, `<style>` blocks, `var(--my-color)` in markup
- Design tokens map to DaisyUI theme variables via `@plugin "daisyui/theme"` format
- Color tokens: `primary`, `primary-content`, `secondary`, `accent`, `neutral`, `base-100..300`, `base-content`
- Layout uses the `layout` component from `resources/layout-reference.md` — never create domain-specific grid components

